            <pb facs="#TL-0512.jpg" n="part4_p038.jpg" xml:id="img_0038" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p038.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_38_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>-507-
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>QN: What Justification do you have for the term " ultimate concern" as a good expression for
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/> ultimate concern? Why are we not better off in saying ultimate concern is faith, rather than vice
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>versa?
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>PT: 1 think I explained that in the very first hours last semester. I said the most laubiguous term
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>probably in all Christianity and all religion and all philosophy of religion, is the term "faith," because
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>faith is confused with belief IN things without evidence. And in order to avoid this confusion,
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>I have rejected using the term "faith" except in a whole book, which I have now written, and which
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>will come out some day [i.e., Dynamics of faith], where all these confusions can be rejected.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_38_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>But if I say faith Now, in this moment here, then the connotations which you have learned from
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>those teachers and parents who say "But you must believe!" are still so strong in the half-conscious
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>of MoST of you that I simply don't dare to use that term. But otherwise you can give me any other
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>term--for instance, in some other context I used the term "encounter with the holy," or "encouter
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>with the ultimate," or something like that, in everything secular and everything which is not
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/> wattimate. All theseÐhrases are possible. But if you use a traditional phrase, then you must first
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>save this traditional phrase.
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>QN: If you were placed in a situation of people belonging predominantly in an unbroken myth, as a
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>minister how would you speak to them?
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>PT: Now there you have asked me the most difficult task of the minister. My only answer, which
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>mixture of
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>practice, is that on the pulpit, where you have a
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>I know a little bit out of
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>people, you have to be extremely cautious in applying, for instance, historical Iriticism to the biblicism
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>legends and myths. In direct teaching, confirmation classes or in adult teaching classes, you can speak
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>openly with them, because those who come are SUppOSEDLY already people who ask questions,
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>pour lʼautre
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>pour lui a
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>cʼest eu quʼil est vrai cette
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_20" n="N020"/>dʼaprès
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_21" n="N021"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_22" n="N022"/>de mon ami
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_23" n="N023"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_24" n="N024"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_25" n="N025"/>dʼun autre vie de
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_26" n="N026"/>de votre beau et très
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_27" n="N027"/>de votre beau et de
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_28" n="N028"/>de Vous avez
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_29" n="N029"/>dʼune manière beau
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_30" n="N030"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_31" n="N031"/>Monsieur de
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_32" n="N032"/>Vous avez
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_33" n="N033"/>dans cette généralité, et cʼest le
               <lb facs="#facs_38_tr_1_tl_34" n="N034"/>dʼordre pour
            </p>
            
